## Required Wireframe Screens

Each group must create the following minimum wireframes and export each screen as PNG.

| Wireframe File | Purpose | Minimum Elements to Show | Related Requirements |
|----------------|---------|--------------------------|----------------------|
| /wireframes/homepage.png | Landing page of the system | Project title, description, Login button, Register button, Navigation bar | FR-01, FR-02 |
| /wireframes/register.png | User registration | Name, Email, Password, Confirm Password, Register button | FR-03 |
| /wireframes/login.png | User login | Email, Password, Login button, Forgot Password link | FR-03 |
| /wireframes/find-groups.png | Search study groups | Search box, Filter, Group list, Join button | FR-04 |
| /wireframes/group-details.png | View group information | Group name, Subject, Description, Members, Join Request button | FR-05 |
| /wireframes/create-group.png | Create a study group | Group name, Subject, Description, Meeting time, Create button | FR-07 |
| /wireframes/my-groups.png | Manage joined groups | Joined group list, Status, Leave Group button | FR-08 |
| /wireframes/profile.png | User profile | Profile information, Edit Profile button, Save button | FR-09 |

## Wireframe Quality Rules

- Use a consistent navigation bar on every screen.
- Keep the layout simple and easy to understand.
- Show realistic sample data instead of empty boxes.
- Every wireframe must match the related system requirements.
- Every screen should connect to the final prototype.
- Wireframes may be created using Figma, Canva, PowerPoint, HTML/CSS, or another suitable design tool.
